{
  "texts": [
    "Previously considered a technical tool, AI now demonstrates its humanoid and creative potential.",
    "García-Peñalvo [33] emphasizes the need to adapt education to use these tools ethically and effectively, fostering co-creation and collaboration between students and technology.",
    "Likewise, Juarez et al. [34] discusses how AI, exemplified by ChatGPT, has integrated into daily and professional life.",
    "The evolution of Large-scale Language Models (LLMs) like ChatGPT requires a reflective approach in teaching, addressing benefits, challenges, and ethical considerations through interdisciplinary collaboration.In this same context, Vera et al. [35] studies the use of ChatGPT to improve English skills in university students.Despite the challenges of traditional methodologies, ChatGPT has shown potential in enhancing English learning.",
    "However, the authors emphasize the need to improve the implementation of these tools to ensure ethical and effective use."
  ]
}